# =============================================================================
# ICP — .dockerignore (repo root)
# =============================================================================
# Slice:    S-00b Foundation Scaffold (T08, Q-7 A LOCKED).
#
# Purpose:  Keep Docker build context lean when the web service builds with
#           `context: ..` (monorepo root) per Q-3 A. Without this file Docker
#           would scan the entire repo (node_modules at root + per-app +
#           per-package, .git history, .next caches, Python venvs, docs,
#           s00b-outputs) — slow uploads to the build daemon AND risk of
#           leaking artifacts into the final image if a `COPY . .` step
#           appears in any Dockerfile.
#
# Scope:    This file affects ALL Dockerfile builds whose context is the
#           monorepo root. Currently only `web` service uses that context
#           (Q-3 A); gateway/ai/mcp use service-local contexts (T03 stubs)
#           and have no need for these exclusions, but the file is harmless
#           there too (their contexts already exclude what is listed).
#
# Pattern:  Mirrors common patterns from `.gitignore` (T01 emit) plus a few
#           Docker-specific extras (Dockerfile itself NOT excluded — needed by
#           the build daemon). Layout grouped by ecosystem.
#
# Source:   docs/00_CONTEXT.md repo layout + .gitignore (T01).
# =============================================================================

# --- Version control --------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- Node / pnpm ------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules
**/node_modules
*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo
dist
**/dist
build
**/build
.turbo
**/.turbo
.pnpm-store
**/.pnpm-store
pnpm-debug.log*
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# --- Next.js ----------------------------------------------------------------
.next
**/.next
next-env.d.ts
out
**/out

# --- Python (apps/ai, apps/mcp — not in web build but harmless) ------------
__pycache__
**/__pycache__
*.py[cod]
**/*.py[cod]
.venv
**/.venv
venv
**/venv
*.egg-info
**/*.egg-info
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache

# --- Env files (NEVER ship .env to image — runtime mount only) -------------
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development
.env.production
# Keep .env.example available in case build process references for defaults.
!.env.example

# --- IDE / editor -----------------------------------------------------------
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# --- OS ---------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# --- Docker -----------------------------------------------------------------
docker-compose.override.yml
docker-compose.override.yaml
# Note: do NOT exclude `Dockerfile` — build daemon needs it.
# Note: do NOT exclude `infra/docker-compose*.yml` — they live outside the
#       web service's COPY targets so they're cost-neutral, but leaving them
#       in keeps the context predictable if a future stage adds debug COPYs.

# --- Test / coverage --------------------------------------------------------
coverage
**/coverage
.nyc_output
*.lcov

# --- Logs / temp ------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
.cache
**/.cache

# --- Docs / planning artefacts (not needed in any image) -------------------
docs
s00-outputs
s00b-outputs
s00b-base
ai-delivery
README.md
*.md

# --- Misc -------------------------------------------------------------------
.editorconfig
.eslintcache
